main event: In 1957, a ground-type rocket-propelled test article penetrated a house in New Orleans, Louisiana, causing damage to the property. The incident was investigated by the United States Air Force and the FBI.
interesting points: The object penetrated a house and embedded itself in the wall, causing damage to the property.
The investigation revealed that the object was a ground-type rocket-propelled test article still partially connected to its parachute lines.
The report mentions the presence of Artifact # 341-6-470 and Artifact # 341-12-476 located in the Artifact Room.
A physical specimen from the New Orleans, LA case was contained in a separate folder.
Another report discussed a bright white light moving slowly in a straight line, possibly indicating a balloon or astronomical object.
witnesses: Mr. A. A. McGee (homeowner), United States Air Force, FBI
photographs: no, the report does not include photographs
